content.detailedDescription:
I was walking our dog, near noon, in our yard. i looked up and around the sky to check for clouds that might indicate incoming weather.  the sky was clear to the west and west southwest.  i look at the sky day and night. 

i saw a bright star like, light reflecting, object, high in the west south western sky.  i figured it to be a weather balloon.  

i saw a large jet plane coming towards it.  i do not know if it was commercial or military.  it was flying very high in the sky, traveling quite fast, from south southwest going north northeast.  not a usual flight path for our area, for commercial planes.

the bright object stayed steady in the same spot.  it did not move or waver as the plane approached.  about 2 to 5 minutes (+-).  not sure.

the light remained in the same spot (location) in the sky until the plane looked to be getting very close and just before the plane got to the lights location, the light suddenly vanished.  totally disappeared.  no trail, nothing.

i kept watching as the plane continued on its flight path.  the light never reappeared.

it was a puzzling event for me and i have wondered about it every since.  i'm interested in a possible explanation.  no strong emotions, feelings or reactions.
content.summary: Bright star like light, high in the wsw sky, in the middle of a clear sunny day.

              so i think i'm watching a satelite then it stops, just sits there in space. this got my attention so i'm watching for maybe 5 seconds and it starts to move again, omg i'm looking at a ufo. i look right at it again and it stops now i can see a second "star" moving in a straight line for the other star. now both stars are on the same path moving toward each other.........I got excited ran in the house to call my wife, it was less than 10 seconds but they were gone. she said she believed me but, don't think i'm crazy .. she encouraged me to email mufon i know what i saw stars don't stop and go nor do man made objects..
if any one else in my area saw something similar to what i saw could you let me know..Thank you

content.detailedDescription:
while walking my dog in front of my house around 9:15pm on friday 5/30/14 i saw what looked to be fireworks at first in the sky less than one mile away above the roof of my neighbors house. quickly i made out several distinct glowing bodies flying close to each other and changing directions. occasional orange colored flares would trail from the white glowing orbs. there were several lights, some were hovering and multiple objects were moving in different directions some crossing paths before changing direction, some flying vertically and some horizontally. 
   one by one the objects would disappear or descend below the roofline of my neighbors home and eventually were all no longer visible from my driveway. i was quite startled when i saw the objects that seemed unexplainable and yelled for my wife to come view the objects as well and she was able to witness them also. also i grabbed my cell phone and recorded a single digital photo and a single digital video on my phone of the objects. immediately after the objects were no longer visible i noticed an airplane in the immediate vicinity of the objects but much closer to me change direction and fly in a circular pattern around the area that i had seen the objects. the objects appeared to be directly over the intracoastal waterway in jacksonville beach florida.
content.summary: Multiple glowing objects in close proximity to each other flying vertically and horizontally discharging orange flares while changing direction of flight.

when i saw what happened it was too surreal... definitely something from a sci-fy movie that one might see. i ask myself, how do they do that?

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend was in the shower and i was just straightening up before we settled into our living room to watch tv when i saw a bright object outside my window much more prominent than the dim looking stars. i took a snap of it from my phone. then i grabbed my video camera stupid thing had no battery so i kept the viewfinder closed to conserve the battery but the zoom was off. i continued filming worthlessly without looking because i wanted to see everything with my own eyes . after about 2 minutes the light went out but i still saw the object very very faintly like trying to see the non lite up side of the crescent moon. 
the object didn't appear to be flair since it was just stationary and not falling. it wasn't a satellite since it was neither moving or as dim as a star.  i was thinking it could have been a chinese fire lantern possibly but we just had some major fires out here in san diego so i'm really not sure it's just simply an unidentified object to me. 

i sure wish something more could have happened so i could better categorize it like floating or falling or zipping across the sky. it just stayed in one spot.

in the photo you can see a bright dot among 2 other dots. the 2 other dots were mars and the bright star spica... according to google sky maps.  the stars can be vaguely seen at 3:30 o'clock and about the 10:30o'clock

i took the photo with my galaxy s4

once however it went north east instead of south east.

all my experiences is like a starlike glowing orb. i thought it could have been a star or similar, but it was moving across the sky, keeping the same distance of height. naturally i believe most objects would pull towards earth due to gravity, but this kept same height and hovered always to the east.

i felt anxious and wanted to record it this time. i recorded the phenomena and put it on youtube for reactions. it felt quite good to actually catch something too.

please tell me what it is i am seeing. a satellite? balloon? i dont think so for obvious reasons, but please contact me regarding this. attaching a video proof of my sighting. the footage has not been altered, edited or manipulated in any way. im sorry for the bad quality. it was obviously dark and hard to record the sky.

content.detailedDescription:
Around 230am i was walking my dog and saw a very bright light in the dark sky at a high altitude. i stared at the object long enough for my eyes to focus and could make out about seven lights in a triangle formation. the triangle looked like the nose was pointed down towards the ground but it was stationary and did not move for about ten minutes. i brought my dog in the house and tried to get a look at it from the back porch but there is a street light that was bright and ruined my night vision. i could still see it but it was very faint. i walked back out to the front of the house where it is darker and the object was gone. 

we live by an airport and i'm used to seeing planes fly over at night but this object did not have blinking lights and was stationary. i would have to guess that it was at an altitude of over 30,000 feet or more. i tried to get a picture with my cell phone camera but was unable to focus in on something at such a great distance.
content.summary: Bright lights in triangle formation at a high altitude.

content.detailedDescription:
Lying on a bed looking straight up out of the window behind my head. just looking at the stars and a formation of stars started to move forwards slowly?  as the formation moved i could see that they were in a triangle shape, the shape moved slowly forwards in a straight line until away from my line of sight.  the object seemed to slightly distort the outline of the triangle shape, as if it was a transparent form. 
the object seemed a long way up and must have been over 400-500 meters wide at that height. no noise was stationary at first, and then moved forward at an undetermined rate and speed.
content.summary: The object seemed a long way up and must have been over 400-500 meters wide at that height. no noise was stationary at first, and then moved forward at an undetermined rate and speed.
